column2: # Function to convert pedigree format and calculate CurAge
# Loop through each pedigree in the list
# Calculate CurAge based on available Year_Birth and death/follow-up information
# If Year_Birth is available, calculate CurAge based on Year_Last_FolUp or YEAR_Death
dat[[i]]$Year_Last_FolUp - dat[[i]]$Year_Birth,  # Use Year_Last_FolUp for alive individuals
dat[[i]]$YEAR_Death - dat[[i]]$Year_Birth),     # Use YEAR_Death for deceased individuals
# If Year_Birth is missing but Age at entrance is available, estimate CurAge
dat[[i]]$Age.at.entrance,  # Use Age.at.entrance for alive individuals
dat[[i]]$Age.at.entrance + (dat[[i]]$YEAR_Death - dat[[i]]$Year_Last_FolUp)),  # Use Age.at.entrance for deceased individuals
# Example usage: Adjust the pedigree data
# Further processing for each data frame in the list
# Convert "Sex" to numeric: 1 for Male ("M") and 0 for Female ("F")
# Remove rows where Sex is NA
# Convert "isProband" to numeric: 1 for proband, 0 otherwise
# Convert "isAff" to numeric: 1 for "True" and 0 for everything else (including NA)
# Adjust "geno" column: 1 for "True", 0 for "False", and NA for unknown
# Ensure "CurAge" and "Age" are within the valid range (1 to 94)
# Ensure valid parent IDs: FatherID and MotherID should be within the existing IDs
# Warn if any invalid parent IDs remain
